Then we find the next number that hasn't been marked as composite, in this =
case it is 3.
Which means 3 is prime, and we mark all proper multiples of 3 as composite.
The next unmarked number is 5, which is the next prime number, and we mark =
all proper multiples of it.
And we continue this procedure until we have processed all numbers in the r=
ow.</p>
