<p>The idea behind is this:
A number is prime, if none of the smaller prime numbers divides it.
Since we iterate over the prime numbers in order, we already marked all num=
bers, which are divisible by at least one of the prime numbers, as divisibl=
e.
Hence if we reach a cell and it is not marked, then it isn't divisible by a=
ny smaller prime number and therefore has to be prime.</p>
